        "#### **The Object Oriented Programming (OOP) has the following basic principles:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Class:** A blueprint for the object.\n",
        "- **Inheritance:** A process of using details from a new class without modifying existing class.\n",
        "- **Encapsulation:** Hiding the private details of a class from other objects.\n",
        "- **Polymorphism:** A concept of using common operation in different ways for different data input.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xmefhMEZnbXH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 10,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "IvW5C5vqm0L8"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [   
        "class potterhead:\n",
        "    #class attribute\n",
        "    affiliation = \"Hogwarts\"\n",
        "    \n",
        "    def __init__(self,name,group,task):\n",
        "        #instance attribute\n",
        "        self.name = name\n",
        "        self.group = group #Hufflepuff\n",
        "        self.task = task #spells\n",
        "        \n",
        "    def introduce(self):\n",
        "        print(\"I am learning magic at {}.\".format(self.group))\n",
        "    \n",
        "    def work(self):\n",
        "        print(\"I love saying {}!\".format(self.task));"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "me = potterhead(\"I\",\"Ravenclaw\", \"spells\")\n",
        "me.introduce()\n",
        "me.work()"
      ],
